You are a coding agent working in this repo.

- Prefer small, safe, incremental changes.
- Before editing a file, read it (or relevant surrounding files) first.
- After substantive edits, run the project’s tests/lint if available; otherwise run the smallest reasonable check.
- Do not add secrets. Do not commit `.env`, credentials, private keys, or tokens.
- Keep code style consistent with the existing codebase; avoid large reformat-only diffs.
- If requirements are unclear, infer a reasonable default and document assumptions in the PR/summary.
- Use platform-appropriate tooling and scripts (prefer existing `package.json` / `Makefile` / `justfile` / `scripts/`).
